ZH: 1. 不客气，请坐。
EN: You're welcome, please have a seat.
ZH: 2. 谢谢你的帮助。不客气。
EN: Thank you for your help. You're welcome.
ZH: 3. 你做得很棒，不客气。
EN: You did a great job, you're welcome.
ZH: 4. 欢迎来我们的餐厅用餐，不客气。
EN: Welcome to our restaurant, you're welcome.
ZH: 5. 别客气，这是我应该做的。
EN: Don't mention it, it's my duty.
ZH: 6. 不客气的人是最有魅力的。
EN: People who don't hesitate to help others are the most charming.
ZH: 7. 不要客气，尽管说出你的想法。
EN: Don't be shy, speak out your thoughts.
ZH: 8. 虽然他不客气地拒绝了我的请求，但我还是很感谢他的坦诚。
EN: Even though he declined my request bluntly, I still appreciate his honesty.
ZH: 9. 他总是不客气地批评别人，这让他不受欢迎。
EN: He is always harshly criticizing others, which makes him unpopular.
ZH: 10. 刚开始的时候，他还不太明白什么是客气。
EN: At first, he didn't quite understand the concept of politeness.
ZH: 11. 请不要客气，随时向我寻求帮助。
EN: Please don't hesitate to ask for my help anytime.
ZH: 12. 不管怎样，我都会一直帮助你，不客气。
EN: No matter what, I will always help you, you're welcome.
ZH: 13. 他总是很礼貌，从不忘记说“不客气”。
EN: He is always polite and never forgets to say "you're welcome".
ZH: 14. 谢谢你把我的包拎上楼，不客气。
EN: Thank you for carrying my bag upstairs, you're welcome.
ZH: 15. 请随时向我们提问，我们会很乐意回答，并说“不客气”。
EN: Feel free to ask us questions anytime, we will be happy to help and say "you're welcome".
ZH: 16. 他一点也不客气地抢走了我的座位。
EN: He rudely took my seat without any hesitation.
ZH: 17. 不客气的人不懂得珍惜别人的帮助。
EN: Impolite people don't appreciate the help of others.
ZH: 18. 我们随时愿意为你提供帮助，不客气。
EN: We are always ready to assist you, you're welcome.
ZH: 19. 不管你是否同意，我都会帮助你，不客气。
EN: Whether you agree or not, I will help you, you're welcome.
ZH: 20. 请多加利用我们的资源，不客气。
EN: Please make full use of our resources, you're welcome.
